[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276438\">Fabrizio Genovese</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/custom.20emojis/near/217421760\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Actually I'm quite angry that the yo kana cannot be easily used in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>LaTeX</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\LaTeX</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.89883em;vertical-align:-0.2155em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">L</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.36em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.904999em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm mtight sizing reset-size6 size3\">A</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.46782999999999997em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7845em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">E</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2155em;\"><span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.125em;\"></span><span class=\"mord textrm\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span> here. I still do believe that it should be the common notation for the Yoneda embedding.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It accepts unicode input:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>よ</mtext><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"/><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"/><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">t</mi></mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mtext>op</mtext></msup></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\" height=\"1em\"></mspace><mi>A</mi><mover><mo stretchy=\"true\">↦</mo><mpadded width=\"+0.6em\" lspace=\"0.3em\"><mtext>よ</mtext></mpadded></mover><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">よ\\colon \\mathscr{C}\\to \\mathsf{Set}^{\\mathscr{C}^\\text{op}} \\\\[1em]\nA \\xmapsto{よ}\\mathscr{C}({-},A)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord cjk_fallback\">よ</span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.1689em;\">C</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.96432em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">S</span><span class=\"mord mathsf\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathsf\">t</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.96432em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1473400000000002em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathscr mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.1689em;\">C</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7385428571428572em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.931em;margin-right:0.07142857142857144em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord text mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">op</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace newline\" style=\"margin-top:1em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1113309999999998em;vertical-align:-0.010999999999999899em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel x-arrow\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.100331em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.322em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight x-arrow-pad\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord cjk_fallback mtight\">よ</span></span></span></span><span class=\"svg-align\" style=\"top:-2.689em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"stretchy\" style=\"height:0.522em;min-width:1.5em;\"><span class=\"halfarrow-left\" style=\"height:0.522em;\"><svg width='400em' height='0.522em' viewBox='0 0 400000 522' preserveAspectRatio='xMinYMin slice'><path d='M40 281 V448H0V74H40V241H400000v40z\nM40 281 V448H0V74H40V241H400000v40z'/></svg></span><span class=\"halfarrow-right\" style=\"height:0.522em;\"><svg width='400em' height='0.522em' viewBox='0 0 400000 522' preserveAspectRatio='xMaxYMin slice'><path d='M0 241v40h399891c-47.3 35.3-84 78-110 128\n-16.7 32-27.7 63.7-33 95 0 1.3-.2 2.7-.5 4-.3 1.3-.5 2.3-.5 3 0 7.3 6.7 11 20\n 11 8 0 13.2-.8 15.5-2.5 2.3-1.7 4.2-5.5 5.5-11.5 2-13.3 5.7-27 11-41 14.7-44.7\n 39-84.5 73-119.5s73.7-60.2 119-75.5c6-2 9-5.7 9-11s-3-9-9-11c-45.3-15.3-85\n-40.5-119-75.5s-58.3-74.8-73-119.5c-4.7-14-8.3-27.3-11-40-1.3-6.7-3.2-10.8-5.5\n-12.5-2.3-1.7-7.5-2.5-15.5-2.5-14 0-21 3.7-21 11 0 2 2 10.3 6 25 20.7 83.3 67\n 151.7 139 205zm0 0v40h399900v-40z'/></svg></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.010999999999999899em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.1689em;\">C</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 217490566,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1605945826
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(LaTeX on Zulip is via a Javascript library called KaTeX, which reimplements part of LaTeX. You can find a very useful list of supported commands <a href=\"https://katex.org/docs/supported.html\">here</a>.)</p>",
        "id": 217495489,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1605954332
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"heart\" class=\"emoji emoji-2764\" role=\"img\" title=\"heart\">:heart:</span> <span aria-label=\"heart\" class=\"emoji emoji-2764\" role=\"img\" title=\"heart\">:heart:</span> <span aria-label=\"heart\" class=\"emoji emoji-2764\" role=\"img\" title=\"heart\">:heart:</span></p>",
        "id": 217498251,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605958994
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Usually font input in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>LaTeX</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\LaTeX</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.89883em;vertical-align:-0.2155em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">L</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.36em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.904999em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm mtight sizing reset-size6 size3\">A</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.46782999999999997em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7845em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">E</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2155em;\"><span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.125em;\"></span><span class=\"mord textrm\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span> is quite more difficult than this. It's still cumbersome to use I guess but at least there's a way</p>",
        "id": 217498257,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605959031
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That was generated by putting this into math mode:</p>\n<p>よ\\colon \\mathscr{C}\\to \\mathsf{Set}^{\\mathscr{C}^\\text{op}} \\\\[1em]<br>\nA \\xmapsto{よ}\\mathscr{C}({-},A)</p>",
        "id": 217509951,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1605978756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I thought that was a joke and then checked the source and it is indeed exactly that <span aria-label=\"rolling on the floor laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f923\" role=\"img\" title=\"rolling on the floor laughing\">:rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:</span><br>\nso as long as you always have the character to hand to copy and paste in, you'll be fine...</p>",
        "id": 217510585,
        "sender_full_name": "[Mod] Morgan Rogers",
        "timestamp": 1605979891
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No joke - I just wanted to make it very explicit to everyone: you can include a unicode character in math mode here, and it'll work.</p>\n<p>(<span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"276071\">@Nathaniel Virgo</span> said this, but he said it so tersely I barely noticed it.)</p>",
        "id": 217510814,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1605980260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277473\">[Mod] Morgan Rogers</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/typesetting.20.E3.82.88/near/217510585\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I thought that was a joke and then checked the source and it is indeed exactly that <span aria-label=\"rolling on the floor laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f923\" role=\"img\" title=\"rolling on the floor laughing\">:rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:</span><br>\nso as long as you always have the character to hand to copy and paste in, you'll be fine...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Indeed, it's still far from being perfect (a macro would be better) but still, at least there's a way <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 217520168,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605994572
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277473\">[Mod] Morgan Rogers</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/typesetting.20.E3.82.88/near/217510585\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>so as long as you always have the character to hand to copy and paste in, you'll be fine...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>or if you're dedicated enough, you can set up Japanese as an input method and type (e.g. on a Mac) <code>ctrl-space</code> <code>y</code> <code>o</code> <code>[enter]</code> <code>ctrl-space</code>. This might be overkill if you don't live in Japan though.</p>",
        "id": 217531346,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1606014512
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276071\">Nathaniel Virgo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/typesetting.20.E3.82.88/near/217531346\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277473\">[Mod] Morgan Rogers</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/typesetting.20.E3.82.88/near/217510585\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>so as long as you always have the character to hand to copy and paste in, you'll be fine...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>or if you're dedicated enough, you can set up Japanese as an input method and type (e.g. on a Mac) <code>ctrl-space</code> <code>y</code> <code>o</code> <code>[enter]</code> <code>ctrl-space</code>. This might be overkill if you don't live in Japan though.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Or, in Emacs, one can run <code>(set-input-method 'japanese)</code>, then type <code>yo</code>, then run <code>(set-input-method nil)</code>. There are less lispy ways to do that but they require memorizing keys that I never use.</p>",
        "id": 217532917,
        "sender_full_name": "Eduardo Ochs",
        "timestamp": 1606017497
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Other alternatives:<br>\n<code>(defun yo () (interactive) (insert \"よ\"))</code><br>\n<code>(defun yo () (interactive) (insert 12424))</code></p>",
        "id": 217532930,
        "sender_full_name": "Eduardo Ochs",
        "timestamp": 1606017575
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wasn't sure offhand what the unicode value for よ was, but I figured it would be in the high 12300s or the low 12400s, so 12424 sounds about right.  The repetition of digits ought to make it easier to remember, now that I've seen it.</p>",
        "id": 217543068,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1606037502
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That makes me back to when I was 10 years old or so and I used alt + 3 numbers I memorised to type the diacritic in \"Pokémon\"</p>",
        "id": 217545698,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1606042134
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276071\">Nathaniel Virgo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/typesetting.20.E3.82.88/near/217531346\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277473\">[Mod] Morgan Rogers</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/typesetting.20.E3.82.88/near/217510585\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>so as long as you always have the character to hand to copy and paste in, you'll be fine...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>or if you're dedicated enough, you can set up Japanese as an input method and type (e.g. on a Mac) <code>ctrl-space</code> <code>y</code> <code>o</code> <code>[enter]</code> <code>ctrl-space</code>. This might be overkill if you don't live in Japan though.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It's even easier on Mac, because you can set up text replacements, e.g. to automatically replace <code>\\yo</code> with <code>よ</code>.</p>",
        "id": 217549908,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1606049328
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275901\">Jules Hedges</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/typesetting.20.E3.82.88/near/217545698\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>That makes me back to when I was 10 years old or so and I used alt + 3 numbers I memorised to type the diacritic in \"Pokémon\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I now feel blessed to have accented vowels on my keyboard</p>",
        "id": 217550126,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1606049692
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>On a UK Mac keyboard there are standard shortcuts for French and German diacritics, which I use all the time</p>",
        "id": 217552978,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1606054314
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you're on Linux (or more specifically, if you use the Compose key) you can set up a custom Compose key sequence, e.g. by making a file named .XCompose in your home folder with the following content:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>include &quot;%L&quot;    # import default rules from system Compose file\n&lt;Multi_key&gt; &lt;y&gt; &lt;o&gt; : &quot;よ&quot; U+3088    # YO kana\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then you can type よ with key combination <code>&lt;Compose key&gt; + &lt;y&gt; + &lt;o&gt;</code>.</p>",
        "id": 217603842,
        "sender_full_name": "Alastair Grant-Stuart",
        "timestamp": 1606122945
    }
]